[Student "S"]
{NORTH should not be tempted to use Jacoby 2NT with this hand. There are only 12 points, and 
the Limit Raise is a perfect way to show a 12 point support hand.

SOUTH has more than enough strength to bid game after NORTH's limit raise. If NORTH had 
mistakenly used a Jacoby 2NT response, SOUTH would probably have tried to reach slam, 
and perhaps gotten too high.}

